{
  "stem": "13817.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What-- what-- every time, what all they did was always counting everybody every morning, every night, every time you went to work.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every time where there was a group moving, you would be counted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You had to-- you had to stand there in-- in columns of five people all the time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every-- the first thing in the morning was if somebody died at night, you had to lay him there so that the five was there to count.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if the count didn't come out, then you stood there for hours.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe somebody couldn't count right or somebody wasn't there or something, somebody didn't see somebody dead in bed or something, so the count didn't come out, you would wait 'til that came out all right.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In the wintertime when it was bitter, bitter cold, you would all stand out there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "People would just fall over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And nobody was-- could even go close and pick them up or anything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You had to stand on-- at attention all the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And everything what they did there was a point of harassment in any way, in which way.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "After 10 days or 8 days-- I don't remember exact dates-- we were loaded with about 500 on-- onto army trucks and driven away from the quarantine and no idea where we were going.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then we arrived in an area what was fenced in with electric fence.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there was a brick building in there and-- and a barrack.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then we were put into that building.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We're told next morning we have to go to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were fitted out with a-- a miner's lamp and got a second uniform.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the next morning, then we were divided into three groups for the first shift, second shift, or night shift.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
